# Environment Setup

## Quick Start

1. Copy `.env` file and add your API key:
   ```bash
   # Edit .env file
   nano .env
   ```

2. Get a free Groq API key:
   - Visit: https://console.groq.com/keys
   - Sign up (free)
   - Create new API key
   - Copy and paste into `.env` file

3. Update `.env`:
   ```
   GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your_actual_key_here
   ```

4. Run server:
   ```bash
   ./venv/bin/python server.py
   ```

## API Key Setup

The `.env` file should contain:
```
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here
```

Replace `your_groq_api_key_here` with your actual API key from Groq.

## Without API Key

If you don't have an API key yet, the app will still work but AI parsing will show an error. You can use the "Quick Start" button instead to load pre-configured lessons.
